body:
I looked at the raw JSON data and did find that file was not created properly, so the problem is deeper in TensorFlow as there is no "input0/1" added to the file for the GPU version (2nd copy of OP):

Here is the proper entry:

> ```
>     {
>         "name": "MatMul",
>         "args": {
>             "input0": "_recv_taking_action/observation_0/_12",
>             "input1": "mydnn/l1_weight/read",
>             "name": "taking_action/mydnn/DNNLayer_1/MatMul",
>             "op": "MatMul"
>         },
>         "pid": 3,
>         "ts": 1470766531877123,
>         "cat": "Op",
>         "tid": 0,
>         "ph": "X",
>         "dur": 52
>     },
> ```

Here is what I think is the bad entry in the JSON with no inputs defined:

> ```
>     {
>         "name": "MatMul",
>         "args": {
>             "name": "taking_action/mydnn/DNNLayer_1/MatMul",
>             "op": "MatMul"
>         },
>         "pid": 5,
>         "ts": 1470766531877204,
>         "cat": "Op",
>         "tid": 0,
>         "ph": "X",
>         "dur": 23
>     },
> ```

Not sure where to go from here.  I am uploading the raw JSON file.
